00033 MTKt_status MtkCacheInit( int32 fid,             
00034               const char *gridname,  
00035               const char *fieldname, 
00036               MTKt_Cache *cache       ) {
00037 
00038   MTKt_status status;       /* Return status */
00039   MTKt_status status_code;      /* Return code of this function */
00040   MTKt_DataBuffer buf_tmp = MTKT_DATABUFFER_INIT;
00041                 /* Temp block data buffer */
00042   MTKt_DataType datatype;   /* Mtk datatype */
00043   int i;            /* Loop index */
00044 
00045 
00046   cache->fid = fid;
00047   cache->gridname = (char *)malloc(strlen(gridname)+1);
00048   strcpy(cache->gridname, gridname);
00049   cache->fieldname = (char *)malloc(strlen(fieldname)+1);
00050   strcpy(cache->fieldname, fieldname);
00051 
00052   cache->block_cnt = 0;
00053  
00054   /* Block cache has NBLOCK+1 elements to make it 1-based, thus i <= NBLOCK */
00055 
00056   for (i = 0; i <= NBLOCK; i++) {
00057     cache->block[i].valid = MTK_FALSE;
00058     cache->block[i].buf = buf_tmp;
00059   }
00060 
00061   /* Set fill value, if available otherwise set to zero */
00062 
00063   status = MtkFillValueGetFid(fid, gridname, fieldname, &(cache->fill));
00064   if (status != MTK_SUCCESS) {
00065     status = MtkFileGridFieldToDataTypeFid(fid, gridname, fieldname,
00066                        &datatype);
00067     if (status != MTK_SUCCESS) MTK_ERR_CODE_JUMP(status);
00068     status = MtkDataBufferAllocate(1, 1, datatype, &(cache->fill));
00069     if (status != MTK_SUCCESS) MTK_ERR_CODE_JUMP(status);
00070     /* Calloc is used to clear the fill buffer, so zero is the default fill */
00071   }
00072 
00073   return MTK_SUCCESS;
00074  ERROR_HANDLE:
00075   return status_code;
00076 }

00087 MTKt_status MtkCachePixelGet( MTKt_Cache *cache, 
00088                   int block,         
00089                   float line,        
00090                   float sample,      
00091                   void *pixel         ) {
00092 
00093   MTKt_status status;       /* Return status */
00094   MTKt_status status_code;      /* Return code of this function */
00095   int rline;            /* Rounded line */
00096   int rsample;          /* Rounded sample */
00097   int nline;            /* Number of lines */
00098   int nsample;          /* Number of samples */
00099   int datasize;         /* Element data size */
00100   char *dptr;           /* Pointer to data buffer */
00101 
00102   if (block <= 0) MTK_ERR_CODE_JUMP(MTK_OUTBOUNDS);
00103 
00104   if (!cache->block[block].valid) {
00105     status = MtkCacheLoad(cache, block);
00106     if (status != MTK_SUCCESS) MTK_ERR_CODE_JUMP(status);
00107   }
00108 
00109   nline = cache->block[block].buf.nline;
00110   nsample = cache->block[block].buf.nsample;
00111   datasize = cache->block[block].buf.datasize;
00112   rline = (int)floor(line+.5);
00113   rsample = (int)floor(sample+.5);
00114 
00115   if (rline < 0 || sample < 0 ||
00116       rline >= nline || rsample >= nsample) MTK_ERR_CODE_JUMP(MTK_OUTBOUNDS);
00117 
00118   dptr = cache->block[block].buf.dataptr;
00119   memcpy(pixel, (void *)&(dptr[rline*nsample*datasize + rsample*datasize]),
00120      datasize);
00121 
00122   return MTK_SUCCESS;
00123  ERROR_HANDLE:
00124   memcpy(pixel, cache->fill.dataptr, cache->fill.datasize); 
00125   return status_code;
00126 }

00137 MTKt_status MtkCacheLoad( MTKt_Cache *cache, 
00138               int block           ) {
00139 
00140   MTKt_status status;       /* Return status */
00141   MTKt_status status_code;      /* Return code of this function */
00142   int iblock;           /* Block to release */
00143 
00144   /* Free a block if cache is full */
00145 
00146   if (cache->block_cnt >= BLOCK_CACHE_MAX) {
00147     iblock = block - BLOCK_CACHE_MAX;
00148     MtkDataBufferFree(&(cache->block[iblock].buf));
00149     cache->block[iblock].valid = MTK_FALSE;
00150     cache->block_cnt--;
00151   }
00152 
00153   /* Read a block */
00154 
00155   status = MtkReadBlockFid(cache->fid, cache->gridname,
00156                cache->fieldname, block,
00157                &(cache->block[block].buf));
00158   if (status != MTK_SUCCESS) MTK_ERR_CODE_JUMP(status);
00159 
00160   cache->block[block].valid = MTK_TRUE;
00161   cache->block_cnt++;
00162 
00163   return MTK_SUCCESS;
00164  ERROR_HANDLE:
00165   return status_code;
00166 }

00176 void MtkCacheFree( MTKt_Cache *cache ) {
00177 
00178   int i;            /* Loop index */
00179 
00180   /* Block cache has NBLOCK+1 elements to make it 1-based, thus i <= NBLOCK */
00181 
00182   for (i = 0; i <= NBLOCK; i++) {
00183     if (cache->block[i].valid) {
00184       MtkDataBufferFree(&(cache->block[i].buf));
00185       cache->block[i].valid = MTK_FALSE;
00186       cache->block_cnt--;
00187     }
00188   }
00189   MtkDataBufferFree(&(cache->fill));
